{
  "stem": "311.3",
  "chunk_idx": 11,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 6.4,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 84,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "So he say look, you're sad, you give 50 years. 49, they say, 1 year you live for the Jew.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 84,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "[BACKGROUND NOISE]",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 85,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So the 50 years is gone.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 85,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "So I don't keep anymore.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 85,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But I get-- I light a candle for my-- for my-- Do you want to tell us your mother and your sister's name, again?",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 86,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes, my mother-- [CRYING] Golda Klainberger from Rahm.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 86,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And my sister name was Hadassah, Hodeh, Hodeh Jachzel.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 86,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "She was the youngest.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 86,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 8 SECONDS] And that was about all.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 87,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "A postcard came in.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 87,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Somehow, my mother had always-- you know, she was very good in correspondence and stuff like this.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 88,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Or she threw out the postcard on her way, you know?",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 88,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And-- or she would give it to somebody who was running behind and through the windows, you know, somehow, you know?",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 89,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "There was a postcard that the-- that we are quite comfortable.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 89,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And-- [SIGHS] that's-- that's about this.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 89,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And take care of yourself.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 89,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And don't stick together.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 89,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And that was the setup.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 89,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "That each one is going to move, separately, so maybe some of us survive.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 89,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "If we would all go together, you know, we might not survive.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 89,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "But one is going to stick up for the other one.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 90,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "That postcard came in to the ghetto.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 90,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And we got the-- all we got is the postcard.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 90,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Matter of fact, after the war, my-- you see, I didn't get me my mother's picture.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 90,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "[SIGHS] [SOBS] After the war, all I got-- and when I went to the committee in Cracow, they had the Kennkarte, you know, from my mother, what she threw out, through the window, with her-- with her picture.",
      "word_count": 38
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 91,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "The will to survive wasn't in my father.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 91,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "You see, I looked at those wires.",
      "word_count": 7
    }
  ],
